Problem:
You are climbing a staircase with n steps.
Each time you can climb either 1 step or 2 steps.
Find the total number of distinct ways to reach the top.

Key Idea:
To reach step n, the last move must be:
1 step from (n-1)
or
2 steps from (n-2)

So the recurrence relation is:

ways(n) = ways(n-1) + ways(n-2)

Base Cases:
ways(1) = 1
ways(2) = 2

This follows the Fibonacci pattern.

Optimized Approach:
Instead of recursion, keep track of the last two values and compute the next one iteratively.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Solved on 10/03/2026
